						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Every programming course nowadays (excluding those specific to games) will only focus on basic logic operations while the students are first learning how to program, and the advanced classes will be all about modern application crap: forms, databases, reports and that kind of shit. most programmers have no clue on how to make a real-time interactive program such as a game.</div>
<br />Man watch your words no reason to be so rude.
<br />
<br />And I've actually had assembly courses in the contex of electronics course, but they really sucked real bad, it was damn easy for me and hard for others as the course sucked terribly. And video games aren't programmed in assembly any longer exept for really old machines when it's needed, so even if you are teached something about video games it won't be assembly, and vice-versa. Assembly is teached for embeded systems applications in electronics.
<br />
<br />And in my country currently nobody learns any actual programming in college unless you choose a special job-oriented college like I did.
<br />
<br />PS : I wonder what they do in those video game college in France, but I'm afraid it's some kind of trap for rich people to fall in, and learn nothing really usefor nor getting a proper diploma recognized internationally when they therminated the scool and passed the exams.</div>

					
